result.execSummary:
The defendant Karmin F Sennott was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500 [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

judgments.action: Guilty Due to No Contest Plea

supervisions.notes: In the event probation is revoked, Defendant would be entitled to Good Time Credit and Huber Privileges. **Based on correspondence from the defendant on March 30, 2018, the Court orders 2 days credit for time served.**

miscConds.notes: Restitution in the amount of $1315.00 is ordered to be repaid in increments of not less than $100.00 per month commencing on August 1, 2017.    In the event that the Defendant is revoked or discharged from probation with outstanding financial obligations, the supervising agent shall notify the Court 10 days prior to the revocation or discharge.  A civil judgment shall be entered against the Defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement action will be used to collect the debt.

Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
Defendant is prohibited from having any contact with the victim as named in the Complaint.
Defendant to comply with any other terms or conditions as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.    DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.
